From MICHAEL BITZ Subject Re Gateway DX V too high a price Well, Gateway faxed me a price sheet just now It seems to be on the higher side, but then again, maybe not DX MHz MB DRAM ns SIMMS expandable to MB MB Western Digital IDE ms Mb DTR Local Bus IDE interface ATI Ultra Pro VL bus with MB VRAM and bit drivers CrystalScan FS color monitor All for This isn't at all too high of a price Keep in mind that you get meg of ram, a local bus IDE and SVGA card, a mb hd, and a monitor The local bus IDE and SVGA really kick butt in Windows I have used a couple of machines with VLB in the past, and all I can do is praise Gateway Mike Bitz Internet Research and Development Dakota State University Bitnet